root.Description:
The player has recently died and has to now be judged by the Devil and the Angel. The player will be given the option to go through a trial and try to get into Heaven. There are 4 different endings.

If the player goes through the trial it'll be asked some questions. SI determine the fate of the player

Dialogues.Utterance: Behave yourself, Lucifer! We have a job to do.
I see you are still high on drugs…
Am I in Skyrim? Fuck yes, I always wanted that.
You ain't the boss of me!
Not again, it’s the third lunatic today, I am out, sayonara
*facepalms to infinity* You are at the crossroad between Heaven and Hell.
Is this the real life *starts dancing to Bohemian Rhapsody*
Everyone has a guaranteed spot in Hell. The real challenge is to get invited into Heaven.
Fuck Heaven, I wanna be a demon.
That is not an answer, that’s a question. Try to keep up, noob!
Shh, leave the questions for the end!
We will ask you about your life on Earth and judge your character. Are you ready?
Who should ask the first question?
What is the answer to this equation x^2 * (d^2/y)/(dx^2) + x * (d/y)/(dx) + (x^2) * y = 0? C’mon, it’s trivial.
He should go first. Oh wait, we are the ones asking the questions.
Enough. I’ll ask you a question.
Why do you want to go to Heaven?
[You have been turned into a demon - Ending 1]
What does that have to do with this?
I don’t know the answer either.
I said in the question that it was *trivial*, I was giving you the answer!
… I want to complain but I can’t tell if it’s correct or not.
Then you must prove you are worthy... Consider this your trial.
Heaven is very feather-y. You wanna die out there? Oh, right...
Your pride is shameful. Off to the hellish boat you go!
Are you kidding me? His pride will sink the boat, you can have him! Just fly him off to Heaven.
Well then… I’m going to Hell.
I thought this religion let people into Heaven if they repented…
Yeah, where are your rules now, oh Holy One?
You haven’t repented! It doesn’t count!
NO! I’ll have a special punishment for you once we’re there!
I bet I can make you lose it.
You’re impatient to get to Heaven though...
That is not what I intended but… How is it, Lucifer? The meme?
We will decide your fate now.
I think we all know where he’s going...
I never did any TikTok dances.
I can eat spicy food without crying.
Because it’s where everyone else is.
And I also believe people become angels when they die.
Don’t you wanna be a hipster?
That is such a vain answer…
Because I get everything that I want.
I must’ve done something good with my life, even if I did something bad too.
You fool! That just shows how lazy you are. And laziness is a mortal sin. Perhaps this trial is worthless after all…
I have to go through a trial? Argh, it’s easier to just go to Hell.
No, wait! Give me another chance!
HA! *lmao* That’s the most cunning reply I’ve heard all day. Listen, kid, I’ll give you a spot as an archdemon if you come with me.
I want to give the trial another try.
Or you can give the trial one more try and go to Heaven…
How bold of you to assume that…
